elements.2211.03017_da25d465450779cb51c1afba7f85c: Learning-based Inverse Rendering of Complex Indoor Scenes with Differentiable MC Raytracing]
elements.2211.03017_2475245c7df53557ed3944d3eab23: Indoor scenes typically exhibit complex, spatially-varying appearance from global illumination, making inverse rendering a challenging ill-posed problem
elements.2211.03017_76cd6311f5719c08533479a3b34f7: This work presents an end-to-end, learning-based inverse rendering framework incorporating differentiable Monte Carlo raytracing with importance sampling
elements.2211.03017_c9ee640202b92a131d2c995345134: The framework takes a single image as input to jointly recover the underlying geometry, spatially-varying lighting, and photorealistic materials
elements.2211.03017_d9f3929b6dab9c42113d094d15c68: Specifically, we introduce a physically-based differentiable rendering layer with screen-space ray tracing, resulting in more realistic specular reflections that match the input photo
elements.2211.03017_415a3e8e230ca7854886615da34e9: In addition, we create a large-scale, photorealistic indoor scene dataset with significantly richer details like complex furniture and dedicated decorations
elements.2211.03017_4e67bc9f1ebaa7809c3762ad2d528: Further, we design a novel out-of-view lighting network with uncertainty-aware refinement leveraging hypernetwork-based neural radiance fields to predict lighting outside the view of the input photo
elements.2211.03017_3bb626b80a2542aa0582638586921: Through extensive evaluations on common benchmark datasets, we demonstrate superior inverse rendering quality of our method compared to state-of-the-art baselines, enabling various applications such as complex object insertion and material editing with high fidelity
elements.2211.03017_99019b04ceeefcb3863ba57364c08: Code and data will be made available at
elements.2211.03017_642b683a7d122e18d7057fd632cdb: Inverse rendering of complex indoor scenes has been a long-standing challenge in computer graphics and vision
elements.2211.03017_750f9618866be3fade28de2905682: Given a single real-world image, global illumination effects such as shadows, specular highlights, and glossy interreflections are baked into the observed pixel values, imposing a particularly difficult task of simultaneously recovering the underlying scene geometry, spatially-varying surface reflectance, and arbitrary unknown illumination
elements.2211.03017_8efc3c51de091549154e2068a331f: Traditional optimization-based approaches rely on dedicatedly designed regularization and hand-crafted priors to tackle this problem
elements.2211.03017_a4811ebb3a73698f0c4f5616fd874: Unfortunately, such methods often fail in real-world scenarios due to overly simplified assumptions, leading to noticeable artifacts in both the decomposition and re-rendered results
elements.2211.03017_d3670490283a59b5e11b3dbf936bd: On the other hand, recent advances in inverse rendering
elements.2211.03017_dff7e58c3e0ed58913c1f6a3a5e96: leveraging deep learning methods have demonstrated impressive results on such scene inference tasks, where the underlying physical priors are supposed to be learnt automatically through an offline, supervised training process, typically on a large-scale, synthetic or labeled real training dataset of complex indoor scenes
elements.2211.03017_f67cbc1b38840c8b1a2e60515b702: Note that, it is extremely difficult, if not impossible, to generate ground truth labels of spatially-varying illumination and materials of an arbitrary real-world scene, and hence one crucial keypoint to the success of such methods is the fidelity and photorealism of the synthetic training data
elements.2211.03017_dc6071cd1c7351950cc418bc1a769: Another essential factor strongly influencing the inference accuracy is the network structure design
elements.2211.03017_48ff5cf8510d72dc1deb8a4f309b3: Intuitively speaking, since inverse rendering is inverting the physical light transport, a physically-based differentiable rendering layer regularizing the parameter space can act as a meaningful prior, improving the robustness and generalization capability of the neural network regarding material and lighting decomposition, and thus also the geometry estimation in return
elements.2211.03017_3c96e662ea50a8de378582ddef28a: Consequently, the performance of these learning-based inverse rendering methods heavily depends on: 1) the quality of the training datasets, and 2) the design of the neural network architecture
elements.2211.03017_30b58cbd46d3e32400794f29f1227: To address the aforementioned challenges, we propose a novel Monte Carlo differentiable rendering layer with importance sampling to faithfully simulate the physical light transport of an indoor scene
elements.2211.03017_908801d45cdc5848cc024d4d27e41: Experiments show that this is especially helpful in restoring the specular reflections of a given scene, and our method produces much more realistic re-rendered results comparing previous baselines

elements.2211.03017_0ac58faad9c512e1b83ffb7cee147: also fails in this task, due to its low-frequency lighting predictions, while our method manages to faithfully recover angular details of the surrounding environment on the inserted sphere.

elements.2211.03017_080932f8e4681971aae194e5eb3bf: We present a learning-based method for inverse rendering of complex indoor scenes
elements.2211.03017_04139badc252a8d4b79ef0082daa8: Our approach handles spatially-varying illumination and faithfully recovers specular reflections thanks to the differentiable Monte Carlo rendering layer, enabling photorealistic editing such as complex object insertion and material change
elements.2211.03017_0b7f023882f66e97a2e2c129f1b4e: Lastly, we introduce a large-scale indoor dataset,
elements.2211.03017_3b6b4f89866c2608aaad6e1edc404: , which contains much richer details than existing alternatives
elements.2211.03017_1cc4caf789eceb19526324806a460: There are some limitations of our method
elements.2211.03017_f7603cf566832c75c9dee192b2ddc: Our out-of-view lighting network is not capable of predicting high-frequency details due to its limited network capacity
elements.2211.03017_2f3e10ad27697290128a7a5cbbb5b: Monte Carlo sampling would also lead to noisy re-render results, and raising the required sample budget can be computationally expensive
elements.2211.03017_e750dce6ded7a2af9c26b9b72a7cb: Further, emission of light sources is not supported currently, which we leave as future work.
